AU  - Noussair, Charles N
T1  - Emotional State and Market Behavior
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfx022
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 22
IS  - 1
SP  - 279
EP  - 309
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We consider the relationship between trader emotions and asset market behavior. We create experimental asset markets with the structure first studied by Smith, Suchanek, and Williams (1988), which is known to generate price bubbles and crashes. To track traders’ emotions in real time, we analyze participants’ facial expressions with facereading software before and while the market is operating. We find that a positive emotional state correlates with purchases and overpricing. Fear correlates with selling, low prices, and price decreases. The experiment confirms the intuition that emotions and market dynamics are closely related.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfx022
ER  - 



